# LucidOS Default /etc/skel Directory
# =============================================================================
# Files in this directory are automatically copied to the home directory
# of each new user created on the system (including the live user 'lucid').
#
# How this directory works:
# - /etc/skel/ is the "skeleton" for new user home directories
# - When 'useradd' or 'adduser' creates a new user, files from /etc/skel/
#   are copied to /home/<username>/
# - For the live session user ('lucid'), live-config does the same
#
# What's included in this skel:
# - .config/           â†’ Application configuration (KDE, GTK, etc.)
# - .local/            â†’ User data and local binaries
# - .bashrc            â†’ Bash configuration (set up by the hook)
# - Desktop/           â†’ Desktop shortcuts and files
#
# IMPORTANT:
# - The actual content of these directories is created by the live hook:
#   config/hooks/live/0100-lucidos-live-user.hook.chroot
# - This README is a placeholder to explain the directory's purpose
# - During the build, the hook populates these directories
#
# If you want to add files directly (without a hook), create them here:
# - live-build/config/includes.chroot/etc/skel/.config/
# - live-build/config/includes.chroot/etc/skel/.bashrc
# etc.
# =============================================================================
